    <item>
      <title>Review of Decathlon BTWIN Triban 100</title>
      <link>https://www.nazim.dev/blog/btwin-triban-100/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 09 Aug 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://www.nazim.dev/blog/btwin-triban-100/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BTWIN Triban 100&lt;/strong&gt; bought from the &lt;strong&gt;Decathlon store&lt;/strong&gt; at Bedok, &lt;strong&gt;Singapore&lt;/strong&gt; was my first drop-bar road bike. This is the most economical and perfect bike for new cyclists starting to ride on the roads and to decide if&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;road.cc had a detailed review of bike 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://road.cc/content/review/decathlon-btwin-triban-100-road-bike-250460&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; which helped immensely in the decision to buy this bike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Another 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://forum.bikeradar.com/discussion/13088608/a-proper-review-of-the-btwin-triban-100&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;thread&lt;/a&gt; on the bikeradar forum also helped me to decide on some of the upgrades for the bike. One of the most useful upgrade was to replace the tyres which came on the bike to something lighter and the replacing the decathlon brake pads with Kool Stop brake pads.&lt;/p&gt;





  











&lt;figure id=&#34;figure-ocbc-cycle-2018&#34;&gt;


  &lt;a data-fancybox=&#34;&#34; href=&#34;https://www.nazim.dev/img/btwin-triban-100/FB_IMG_1525584353180-M.jpg&#34; data-caption=&#34;OCBC Cycle 2018&#34;&gt;


  &lt;img src=&#34;https://www.nazim.dev/img/btwin-triban-100/FB_IMG_1525584353180-M.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;  &gt;
&lt;/a&gt;


  
  
  &lt;figcaption&gt;
    OCBC Cycle 2018
  &lt;/figcaption&gt;


&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-note&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pros:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Price - A lot of bike for very little money!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Beginner Friendly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stable handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-warning&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cons:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Index shifter needs getting used to&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Struggles to climb&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Size S came only with one water bottle mount&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Kilometers Used:&lt;/strong&gt; 3,244.50 KMs / 2016.03 Miles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Total Cost:&lt;/strong&gt; SGD 300.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;





  











&lt;figure id=&#34;figure-newbie-mistakes---padded-seat-cover--stand&#34;&gt;


  &lt;a data-fancybox=&#34;&#34; href=&#34;https://www.nazim.dev/img/btwin-triban-100/IMG_20180111_202213-4K.jpg&#34; data-caption=&#34;Newbie mistakes - Padded Seat Cover &amp;amp; Stand&#34;&gt;


